===Etymology===
Derived from Arabic {{Arab|[[صفة]]}} (''súffa'', [[sofa]], long seat made of stone or brick). The word may have entered European languages via Turkish or through the Moorish occupation of Spain.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|sō'fə}}, {{IPA|/ˈsəʊfə/}}, {{SAMPA|/"s@Uf@/}}
* {{audio|en-us-sofa.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|əʊfə}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[upholster]]ed seat, typically having sides and back, long enough to accommodate two or more people.

